Patients at Wolfson Children's Hospital are able to remotely play with animals at the Jacksonville Humane Society shelter . 
  System uses high-definition cameras and interactive toys . 
  Children can control three different cat toys at the shelter with the push of a button . 
  Watch on the TV as the animals react and play with them . 
  Idaho firm behind the system has already installed its system in 10 animals shelters across the US . 
 